President Muhammadu Buhari has signed the Public Holiday Amendment Act, declaring June 12 of every year a public holiday and Democracy Day. Presidential aide on National Assembly (Senate), Senator Ita Enang, stated this while briefing State House correspondents on Monday. He said with the assent to the amendment, May 29 has been removed as a public holiday. “By the act amended and signed by Mr. President, May 29 is no more a public holiday. June 12 is now a public holiday and the country’s Democracy Day,” he said. The assent came 48 hours to the celebration of the country’s maiden Democracy Day. Bill to make June 12 Democracy Day passes 2nd reading Reps ratifies June 12 as Democracy Day Senate approves June 12 as Democracy Day Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin